Class Eval

  • java.lang.Object
    • Eval

  • public class Eval
extends java.lang.Object
    Class Eval is a program that evaluates a cryptographic function for a single input. It is intended for unit testing the implementation of the cryptographic function.

    Usage: java Eval "function" A B

    The function argument is a constructor expression for the Function object that implements the cryptographic function to be tested. (For further information about constructor expressions, see class edu.rit.util.Instance.)

    The A argument is the function's A input value (hexadecimal).

    The B argument is the function's B input value (hexadecimal).

    The Eval program computes and prints the function's C output (hexadecimal) for each round of the function.
